{% extends "_widget_base.md.jinja" %}

{% block demo_examples %}
## Examples

### Basic
Without a `path_pattern`, the matrix is anchored at `path_start`: column 0 is the first
step of every path, and each column to the right is one step further in.

<DemoWidget cmd={`stream.step_matrix()`} path="/docs-demos/widgets/step-matrix/basic.html" height={660} />

### Path pattern - central event
A single event as `path_pattern` re-centers the matrix on that event instead of
`path_start`: column 0 is always `purchase`, negative columns are the steps leading up
to it, positive columns are what follows.

<DemoWidget cmd={`stream.step_matrix(path_pattern="purchase")`} path="/docs-demos/widgets/step-matrix/path_pattern_central.html" height={660} />

### Path pattern - funnel patterns
Chaining several anchors with `.*` renders one matrix block per anchor, side by side,
so you can follow a multi-step funnel across blocks.

<DemoWidget cmd={`stream.step_matrix(path_pattern="payment_details->.*->shipping_details->.*->purchase", step_window=2)`} path="/docs-demos/widgets/step-matrix/path_pattern_funnel.html" height={660} sidebarOpen={false} />

### Path pattern - drop-off points
`path_pattern="path_end"` centers on where paths end, so the columns to the left show
what users tend to do right before dropping off (or completing their path).

<DemoWidget cmd={`stream.step_matrix(path_pattern="path_end")`} path="/docs-demos/widgets/step-matrix/path_pattern_dropoff.html" height={660} />

### Diff mode
Passing `diff` splits paths into two segments and shows the difference between them at
each step, making it easy to spot where the segments' behavior diverges.

<DemoWidget cmd={`stream.step_matrix(diff=["platform", "mobile", "desktop"])`} path="/docs-demos/widgets/step-matrix/diff.html" height={660} />

{% endblock %}
